SIMPLE: uneven
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uneven
<hw>Un*e"ven</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>unefen</ets>. See <er>Un-</er> not, and <er>Even</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not even; not level; not uniform;
rough; <as>as, an <ex>uneven</ex> road or way; <ex>uneven</ex>
ground</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not equal; not of equal length.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hebrew verse consists of <qex>uneven</qex> feet.</q>
<rj><qau>Peacham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not divisible by two without a remainder; odd; --
said of numbers; <as>as, 3, 7, and 11 are <ex>uneven</ex>
numbers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><wordforms><wf>Un*e"ven*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*e"ven*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unevitable</ent>⟦br⟧
